  "body": "### Background\r\n\r\nValidator accounts management is the weakest part of our codebase as it stands today, providing very little in terms of UX, security, and documentation necessary for production. Among some of the questions we receive on a frequent basis are:\r\n\r\n- How can I move around my validator to a different computer? Is there something I need to do to move my withdrawal key to cold storage?\r\n- I had an account on a different computer I want to move to this computer, but the account had a different password\r\n- How can I list my public keys / private keys?\r\n- How can I regenerate my deposit data for my validator?\r\n- What is the keymanager? What are keymanageropts? What are all these flags? There is no documentation for any of this\r\n- Is there documentation for accounts management? How can I provide a remote signer?\r\n\r\n## TODOs\r\n\r\n### General\r\n\r\n- [x] Split accounts v1/ and v2/ code into separate packages\r\n- [x] Define and implement `prysm validator accounts-v2` commands: `new, list, import, export`\r\n- [x] Ensure all commands work in both interactive vs. non-interactive\r\n- [x] Define and implement `prysm validator wallet-v2` commands `create, edit-config`\r\n- [x] Integrate into validator runtime\r\n- [x] Add comprehensive accounts-v2 documentation to https://docs.prylabs.network\r\n- [x] Support altona key creation with feature flags\r\n\r\n### Direct Keymanager (Non-HD)\r\n\r\n- [x] Fully implement with proper tests and godocs\r\n- [x] Print withdrawal keys to stdout instead of persisting them\r\n- [x] Sanitize and enforce secure passwords\r\n- [x] Allow for regeneration of deposit data\r\n- [x] Allow adding validator keys while validator client is running #5202\r\n\r\n### Remote Keymanager\r\n\r\n- [x] Implement a reference example using gRPC: see [prysmaticlabs/remote-signer](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/remote-signer)\r\n- [x] Implement in Prysm, allowing for initialization of a new remote keymanager by passing in required options such as a grpc remote address and TLS cert paths\r\n- [x] Add comprehensive tests and godocs\r\n\r\n### Derived Keymanager (HD hierarchical deterministic)\r\n- [x] Implement according to [EIP-2333](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2333)",
